    "The backbone network's first layer, called the focusing layer, is utilized to speed up training and simplify model calculations.",
    "The following objectives are achieved by it: The three-channel picture is divided into four slices for each channel using a slicing method.",
    "The output feature map was generated using the convolutional layer comprised of 32 convolution kernels.",
    "Then, the four sections are connected in depth using concatenation, with the output feature map having a size of.",
    "After that, the results are output into the next layer using the Hardswish activation functions and the batch normalization (BN) layer."
